@database "mftp.guide"

@Index Index

@Node Main "mftp documentation"

                     @{u}mftp  -  MUI File Transfer Protocol@{uu}

           Version 1.34         © by Michael Neuweiler  1995 - 1996
           31th March 1996             email: dolphin@zool.unizh.ch

   @{b}mftp@{ub} is a ftp client for the @{"AmiTCP" link "MUI AmiTCP"} protocol stack.
   Useful features as directory caching, adjustable transfer buffer size,
   @{"MUI" link "MUI AmiTCP"} interface and a lot more make it much easier to work with than with
   standard @{i}command line@{ui} ftp clients.

      @{" Copyright    " link "Copyright"}              Copyright and shareware conditions
      @{" Register     " link "Register"}              How to register
      @{" Author       " link "Author"}              How to reach the author

      @{" Requirements " link "Requirements"}              What you need to run mftp
      @{" Installation " link "Installation"}              How to install mftp
      @{" Operation    " link "Operation"}              Help on operation

      @{" ToDo         " link "ToDo"}              What is still not implemented
      @{" Bugs         " link "Bugs"}              Known Bugs
      @{" Updates      " link "Updates"}              Where to find updates of mftp
      @{" MUI / AmiTCP " link "MUI AmiTCP"}              About MUI and AmiTCP
@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Copyright" "Copyright and shareware conditions"

@{u}Copyright and shareware conditions@{uu}


@{b}Copyright:@{ub}

 Copyright  ©  1995 - 1996 by Michael Neuweiler

 This program is @{b}shareware@{ub}.
 mftp may only be redistributed as complete archive with
 all copyright notices left intact.


@{b}Shareware:@{ub}

 The {@b}evaluation period@{ub} for this program is @{b}30 days@{ub}.
 Which means you are allowed to use mftp for 30 days without
 registering. After this period you either have to @{"register" link "Register"}
 or you have to remove the program.
 The program is @{b}not crippled@{ub} in any way. Only a requester
 will appear after you started mftp.


@{b}Waranty:@{ub}

 The @{"author" link "Author"} won't take any responsability for any problems caused by
 mftp. Although it has been tested and optimised it is likely that
 there are still some @{"bugs" link "Bugs"} left which might crash your or the remote
 system and cause data loss.
@EndNode

@Remark ============================================================================

@Node "Register" "How to register"

@{u}How to register mftp@{uu}


 mftp is @{"Shareware" link "Copyright"}.
 After the evaluation period of 30 days you are no longer
 allowed to use the program if you're not registered.

 The registration fee is $10 US  (or 10.- SwissFrancs)

 You will receive a key files which you can copy to one
 of the following directories: PROGDIR: , S: , DEVS: , L:
 KEYPATH: , KEYFILES:  or to any directory where the
 environment variable "Keypath" or "Keyfiles" points to.

 The key file will usually be sent uuencoded by email.
 If you prefer a floppy you will have to include an
 envelope with your address and the right postage on it.

The safest way would be a money transfer to my @{b}bank account@{ub}:

   Bank   :  Swiss Credit (Schweizerische Kreditanstalt)
   Account:  0872 - 867811-40
   Branch :  Zuerich, Wollishofen

Another would be a money transfer to my @{b}postcheck account@{ub}:

   To     :  PTT Switzerland   (PTT Schweiz)
   Account:  80-224959-4

Or just simply send me a bill by @{b}standard mail@{ub} to :

   Michael Neuweiler
   Hauriweg 6
   CH-8038 Zuerich
   Switzerland

 @{b}Checks{@ub} are only accepted if you add at least
 the handling fee to the amount. (i.e. for Eurochecks
 you'll have to add $10 US)  !!

@EndNode

